The paper deals with the mathematical foundations of inconsistency indicators in pairwise comparisons matrices, which is a topic that falls under multiple sub-fields of computer science. The use of axioms and formal logic suggests a focus on mathematical structures and algorithms, which is characteristic of cs.MS (Mathematical Software) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The study also involves improving the axiomatization proposed by previous authors, which indicates a focus on theoretical research, which is characteristic of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the study proposes a new axiom that prevents approximation error aberrations, which suggests a focus on practical applications, which is characteristic of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
